---
// About section with bio and credentials
---

<section id="about" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-serif text-[var(--color-forest-green)] mb-4"
        >
          Meet Attorney Kristie Gotwald
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-start">
        <!-- Left: Professional Headshot -->
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <img
            src="/headshot.jpeg"
            alt="Kristie Gotwald, Attorney at Law"
            class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full"
          />
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-4 rounded-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-forest-green)] mb-2">
                Licensed In:
              </h3>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-gray-700">
                <li>• Oklahoma</li>
                <li>• New York</li>
                <li>• Ohio</li>
                <li>• Southern District of Ohio (Federal)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-[var(--color-gold)] bg-opacity-10 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-forest-green)] mb-2">
                Recognitions:
              </h3>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-gray-700">
                <li>• National Trial Lawyer's Top 40 under 40</li>
                <li>• Dayton's Best Attorney Nominee</li>
                <li>• Bar Association Leadership</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Bio Content -->
        <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-6">
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Hailing from the Adirondack Mountains in Upstate New York, Kristie
              Gotwald moved to Ohio in 2007 to study at Cedarville University,
              where she completed her four-year degree in just two and a half
              years. She then spent the next several years moving around the
              country as a military spouse, earning her Juris Doctor from the
              University of Oklahoma College of Law in 2012.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Attorney Gotwald has experience in civil, criminal, and family
              law. She defends the accused from traffic through felony cases and
              has been named to the National Trial Lawyer's Top 40 under 40 list
              for Ohio's criminal defense attorneys. She has been nominated
              multiple years as Dayton's Best Attorney and has served positions
              of leadership with both the Dayton and Greene County Bar
              Associations.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Gotwald knows the stresses and emotions involved when it comes to
              someone's family. She navigates her clients through some of the
              most difficult times in their lives, dealing with custody,
              divorce, or allegations from the State.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              In her free time, she enjoys spending time with her family and
              running them to all of their extracurriculars.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Notable Achievement -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-forest-green)] text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-serif mb-2">
              Notable Achievement
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-100">
              Attorney Gotwald has been on multiple murder cases and
              successfully had a man's conviction overturned after he spent 17
              years in prison for a crime he didn't commit.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Family Photo -->
          <div class="mt-8">
            <img
              src="/family.jpeg"
              alt="Kristie Gotwald with family"
              class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full max-w-md mx-auto md:mx-0"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
